Summary: 
Misir Mardanov (born October 3, 1946) is an Azerbaijani mathematician, university professor, and politician. He served as the Minister of Education of Azerbaijan from March 1998 to April 2013, and previously as the Rector of Baku State University from 1996 to 1998. He is currently the director of the AMEA Institute of Mathematics and Mechanics (since 2013). Additionally, he was a long-time member of the New Azerbaijan Party's leadership and has received honors such as the 'Honored Scientist of the Republic of Dagestan' (2011) and the 1st degree 'For Service to the Motherland' order (2021). This comprehensive overview provides the essential biographical details for cross-referencing with any given clues.
